    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does the 50% deductible waiver actually work?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        When you receive care outside the US, your deductible is automatically cut in half. A $2,500 deductible becomes $1,250 for that claim. This applies per policy year, not per claim—once you've hit your effective deductible (half the stated amount outside US), you're covered at 100% for the rest of the year.
      </p>
    </div>

